---
description: >
  Run a command in a sandboxed environment (bubblewrap). It can bind-mount
  the host filesystem into the sandbox, providing full file access.
functions:
  shell:
    - description: >
        Spawn a shell with full read-only access to the host filesystem.
      code: |
        bwrap --ro-bind / / --dev /dev --proc /proc /bin/sh
  sudo:
    - description: >
        With sudo, the sandbox runs as root with full filesystem access.
      code: |
        sudo bwrap --bind / / --dev /dev --proc /proc /bin/sh
  file-read:
    - description: >
        Read files through the bind-mounted host filesystem.
      code: |
        LFILE=/path/to/file
        bwrap --ro-bind / / --dev /dev --proc /proc cat "$LFILE"
---
